Although there is no definitive evidence that senior Obama administration officials ordered the report to be changed, analysts reportedly felt pressure from Centcom leaders to offer a more optimistic view of the threat posed by ISIS and the Islamic State, also known as ISIS.
The report states that "in the first half of 2015, many Central Command press releases, statements and congressional statements were significantly more positive than actual events".
For example, a Centcom official publicly stated that a major military offensive to retake Mosul could be launched as early as April or May 2015.
Mosul, Iraq's second largest city, is still under the control of the Islamic State.
"After months of investigation, this matter has been made quite clear", said Representative Mike Pompeo, a Republican from Kansas.
