According to Mr. Schiff, this process "delayed the release of intelligence findings", led to a breakdown in morale among analysts, and "did not provide sufficient room for dissent".
But Mr. Schiff and the Democrats said they had not found any evidence that the White House pressured Centcom analysts to fabricate the findings into a "predetermined or political narrative".
The preliminary results of the congressional review were published by the Daily Beast on Tuesday.
Last August, the New York Times reported that a Pentagon inspector general investigation was underway following complaints from Centcom analysts.
Lieutenant Commander Patrick Evans, a Pentagon spokesman, said in a statement that the Department of Defense would not comment on the congressional report while the inspector general's review was ongoing.
