Mr. Farrell said the situation would get much worse if the federal government's decision was not reversed.
"Queensland's community legal support centres are chronically underfunded, meaning thousands of people are unable to access the vital services they need", he said.
People in violent relationships, struggling with the forces that are holding them back, families in the process of separation, and workers who have been unfairly fired... all face problems with a legal dimension and are not getting the help they need, according to this report.
The federal government will cut funding by 30 percent starting in June 2017, which means thousands of vulnerable Queenslanders will be forced to deal with more complex legal issues without help.
We urge the Attorney General and Senator George Brandis of Queensland to immediately lift these funding cuts so that people can get the support they need when they face a legal challenge.
